<h1 id="gb-00002-set-up-sales-tax-groups-for-reverse-charge-vat">GB-00002 Set up sales tax groups for reverse charge VAT</h1>


<p>This task walks you through setting up reverse charge sales tax groups for purchasing and sales purposes. This walkthrough was created using the demo company GBSI.</p>
<p>This task requires that the following sales tax codes are created for Reverse charge purposes.</p>
<p>REV17.5 – positive value</p>
<p>REV-17.5 – negative value</p>
<p>The sales tax group 'RC-VAT' should already contain both +ve and -ve sales tax codes.</p>
<p>In this task you'll create a new sales tax group that will contain a +ve sales tax code.</p>
<ol>
<li>Go to Tax &gt; Indirect taxes &gt; Sales tax &gt; Sales tax groups.</li>
<li>In the list, find and select the desired record.
<ul>
<li>For this example, select 'RC-VAT'.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Expand or collapse the Setup section.
<ul>
<li>Verify that the following sales tax codes exist for Reverse charge purposes:  REV17.5 – positive value  REV-17.5 – negative value</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>In the list, find and select the desired record.
<ul>
<li>Select the 'REV-17.5' sales tax code. This must be a sales tax code with a negative value.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Click Edit.</li>
<li>Select the Reverse charge check box.</li>
<li>Click Save.</li>
<li>Click New.</li>
<li>In the Sales tax group field, type a value.
<ul>
<li>For this example, enter 'RC-VAT-AR'.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>In the Description field, type a value.
<ul>
<li>For this example, enter &quot;Reverse charge VAT sales&quot;.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Click Add.</li>
<li>In the Sales tax code field, click the drop-down button to open the lookup.</li>
<li>In the list, find and select the sales tax code REV17.5 with positive value</li>
<li>In the list, click the link in the selected row.</li>
<li>Select the Exempt check box.</li>
<li>Select the Reverse charge check box.</li>
<li>Click Save.</li>
</ol>
